    "This signal is a regime filter (AVOID/SKIP trading) rather than entry/exit rules. It requires: (1) MA slope calculation over 10 bars which requires multi-bar historical comparison not supported by allowed operators, (2) support/resistance band detection which requires dynamic level identification not in the allowed indicator set, (3) price crossing MA on both sides within 5 bars which requires multi-bar pattern matching. The position_size_multiplier of 0.0 indicates this should reduce or skip trades entirely during RANGING regime, but the backtest engine schema requires explicit entry/exit conditions rather than position sizing modifiers.": 1,
    "Signal requires detection of multiple support level tests (3+) and comparison of bounce highs across a multi-bar lookback window. This requires: (1) dynamic support level identification, (2) counting the number of times price tests that level within a rolling window, and (3) tracking and comparing previous bounce highs. These operations require historical array access, local variable state, or custom support/resistance detection logic that cannot be expressed using only the allowed indicators and simple 3-field condition syntax. The allowed indicator set does not include support/resistance detection, count operators, or multi-bar comparative logic.": 1,
    "Signal requires tracking successive bounce highs and comparing current bounce high against previous bounce high heights. This requires: (1) dynamic identification of support bounce points across multiple lookback periods, (2) measurement of bounce amplitude (high - support level) for each bounce, and (3) comparison of current bounce amplitude vs. prior bounce amplitude to detect deterioration pattern. The allowed indicators do not include a bounce detection mechanism, bounce height measurement, or historical bounce tracking capability. Standard price/MA/oscillator indicators cannot reliably identify swing lows (support bounces) or measure progressive diminishment of bounce heights across consecutive cycles. This pattern requires custom swing-point analysis unavailable in the allowed indicator set.": 1,
    "Signal requires detection of: (1) range boundary identification with horizontal support/resistance levels, (2) tracking of equal highs/lows formation, (3) breakout attempt detection with follow-through analysis, and (4) failed breakout pattern recognition. These require multi-bar pattern analysis and statistical comparison not available in single-bar indicators. Donchian channels provide range boundaries but cannot detect failed breakout attempts or follow-through validation.": 1,
    "Signal requires detection of: (1) equal extremes count (minimum 2), (2) follow-through definition/threshold, (3) time-to-confirm failed breakout - none of which can be directly expressed with available indicators. Donchian channels approximate range boundaries, but cannot quantify equal highs/lows or measure breakout follow-through magnitude/duration.": 1,
